a sets is not possible. The study showed that countries use varying defnitions for climate fnance and diferentiate between fnance allocated for mitigation and adaptation. An example of this is the Philippines, which has a general defnition of climate fnance (established in the People\u2019s Survival Fund), and four diferent categories are used: adaptation, mitigation, adaptation and mitigation combined and disaster risk reduction (DRR) (which is included as part of adaptation fnance. In the case of Colombia there has been a long debate about the defnition of climate fnance. In recent years the country has developed a process to integrate a methodology to classify and measure climate fnance. The methodology uses the operational defnition created by the Standing Committee \u201cClimate Finance aims at reducing emissions, and enhancing sinks of GHG and aims at reducing vulnerability of, and maintaining and increasing the resilience of, human and ecological systems to negative climate change impacts\u201d (SCF, 2016:16). However, an important step that Colombia took was the integration of a top down approach that also follows the international defnition from the Rio Markers of the OECD. The methodology also uses a bottom up approach, using the actual defnition of activities that were included in the national policies to create a match between these two perspectives. Nepal does not have a strict defnition of what counts as climate fnance. This has been a huge bottleneck in accounting climate fnance in the country. Often, the confusion leads to huge overlap between climate fnance and regular development assistance. It is clear that the defnition of climate fnance remains crucial for countries to be able to track fnancial fows.", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "6321f4e4-3597-494c-b503-c9d5fbefd609": {"__data__": {"id_": "6321f